Certainly! Here are the grading criteria for the given student report based on the report title and task:

1. Clear and concise report title:
The report title should accurately and concisely reflect the content of the report. It should be specific and not too broad or too narrow in scope.
(Max 1 point)
2. Appropriate task:
The task should be clearly stated and relevant to the report title. It should be specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART).
(Max 1 point)
3. Appropriate research:
The report should include relevant and reliable sources that support the task. Sources should be properly cited and referenced, and the credibility of the sources should be evaluated.
(Max 1 point)
4. Coherent structure:
The report should have a clear and logical structure that guides the reader through the content. It should include an introduction, body, and conclusion.
(Max 1 point)
5. Clear and concise writing:
The report should be written in clear and concise language that is easily understood. Technical terms should be defined, and sentences should be concise and to the point.
(Max 1 point)

Note: Each criterion will be graded on a binary scale, with a score of 1 point for fulfillment and 0 points for non-fulfillment. The final score will be calculated based on the sum of all fulfilled criteria, with a maximum score of 5 points.